19:T99f,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Can AI be implemented faster than 30 days?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Some businesses try to compress the planning phase — and sometimes succeed in deploying an AI tool in days. The question is whether what they deploy solves the right problem in the right workflow with the right oversight structure. Speed without planning is what produces the failed AI pilots that cost more than they save. 30 days of planning prevents 6 months of misdirected implementation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What slows down AI implementation most?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Data readiness is the most common bottleneck. Discovering that the data required for a specific use case does not exist in accessible, structured form — after the planning process has already selected that use case — adds 4–8 weeks of data preparation. The AI Navigator framework addresses this in Week 1 by assessing data readiness before committing to a use case."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many AI use cases can be implemented simultaneously?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For most SMEs, one Tier 1 use case at a time is the right pace. Attempting multiple simultaneous implementations splits team attention, complicates the feedback loops, and makes it harder to attribute results to specific changes. Once the first use case is live and stable, the second can begin."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the minimum viable AI implementation for a small business?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The minimum viable AI implementation is a single, well-defined use case that solves a clearly identified workflow problem. A WhatsApp auto-responder that handles 70% of routine enquiries. An AI description generator that produces bilingual product copy in hours rather than days. The value is real and measurable even at the smallest scale."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does AI require ongoing maintenance after implementation?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. AI systems require monitoring, feedback processing, and periodic recalibration as business conditions change. The governance framework established in Chapter 11 of the AI Navigator defines the ongoing management cadence — typically a monthly review of performance metrics and a quarterly assessment of whether the use case scope needs expanding."}}]}f:[["$","$L2",null,{"id":"faq-schema","type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$19"}}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"article-wrap","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"breadcrumb","aria-label":"Breadcrumb","children":[["$","a",null,{"href":"/","children":"Home"}],["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":"true","children":" › "}],["$","a",null,{"href":"/resources/","children":"Resources"}],["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":"true","children":" › "}],["$","span",null,{"children":"How Long Does It Take to Implement AI in a Business?"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"children":"How Long Does It Take to Implement AI in a Business?"}],[["$","p","0",{"children":"The honest answer has two parts. Planning takes 30 days. Implementation takes 4–8 weeks for Tier 1 use cases, 2–4 months for Tier 2, and 6–12 months for Tier 3."}],["$","p","1",{"children":"The distinction matters because most businesses conflate planning and implementation into a single undifferentiated 'AI project' — and then wonder why timelines are unpredictable. They are unpredictable because the planning has not been done."}]],"$L1a",["$L1b","$L1c","$L1d","$L1e"],"$L1f","$L20","$undefined","$L21","$L22"]}]]
